❗️The Verkhovna Rada of Ukraine adopted as a basis the draft law on expanding the powers of local self-government bodies to support the security and defense sector of Ukraine (No. 9559-d), — Committee on the organization of state power. defense of Ukraine; ✔️ ensuring the possibility:
- appointment of a village, settlement, city mayor to the position of head of the relevant military administration of the settlement without dismissal from the position;
- appointment of civil servants and local self-government officials who are on leave without salary;
- conducting remote meetings of local councils, their executive bodies, permanent deputy commissions to consider issues related to urgent changes to the local budget, urgent work to eliminate the consequences of emergency situations. 📲Details

🇺🇦Ukrainians won three medals of the World Cup in Parajudo, — Youth and Sports Committee. National Paralympic national judo team won high awards at the ranking for the Paralympics-2024 Judo World Cup among the visually impaired, which will take place from March 28 to April 2, 2024 was held in Antalya (Turkey).

178 athletes with disabilities from 41 countries took part in the competition, seven Ukrainian parajudokas won two silver and one bronze awards.

Oleksandr Nazarenko — w/c up to 90 kg (J2), silver;

Khorava David - 60 kg (J2), silver;

Angela Havrysyuk — junior athlete up to 57 kg (J1), bronze. Congratulations to the athletes of the national paralympic judo team of Ukraine on their victories at the World Cup: another important step towards licenses for Paris-2024 has been passed! 👏 Source: National Committee of Sports for the Disabled of UkraineTelegram/ Facebook/ Site /Instagram/ X
